01:00:33.579 --> 01:00:35.581 line:90% position:50% align:center
For this month’s video postcard,

01:00:35.581 --> 01:00:38.318 line:90% position:50% align:center
we travel to Guatemala in Central America.

01:00:39.686 --> 01:00:43.022 line:90% position:50% align:center
What aspects
of Jehovah’s creation do you enjoy?

01:00:43.022 --> 01:00:44.357 line:90% position:50% align:center
jungles?

01:00:45.158 --> 01:00:46.492 line:90% position:50% align:center
beaches?

01:00:47.460 --> 01:00:50.830 line:90% position:50% align:center
mountains? rain forests?

01:00:50.830 --> 01:00:53.333 line:90% position:50% align:center
Guatemala has them all!

01:00:53.333 --> 01:00:57.537 line:90% position:50% align:center
It even has volcanoes
—lots of volcanoes!

01:00:57.537 --> 01:01:00.606 line:90% position:50% align:center
Southern Guatemala has a string of 27.

01:01:02.108 --> 01:01:05.778 line:90% position:50% align:center
The first missionaries arrived in 1945.

01:01:05.778 --> 01:01:07.113 line:90% position:50% align:center
By 1958,

01:01:07.113 --> 01:01:11.184 line:90% position:50% align:center
there were more than 700 Witnesses
in three circuits.

01:01:11.184 --> 01:01:14.187 line:90% position:50% align:center
Difficulties arose
in the 1980’s when the government

01:01:14.187 --> 01:01:18.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
organized armed civilians
to patrol communities.

01:01:18.057 --> 01:01:20.259 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some of our brothers
were threatened with death

01:01:20.259 --> 01:01:23.129 line:90% position:50% align:center
if they did not join the civil patrols.

01:01:23.129 --> 01:01:25.465 line:90% position:50% align:center
But they stood firm! 

01:01:26.899 --> 01:01:29.869 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, about 40,000 publishers

01:01:29.869 --> 01:01:33.573 line:90% position:50% align:center
serve in more than 850 congregations.

01:01:33.573 --> 01:01:36.909 line:90% position:50% align:center
Their preaching methods
are as diverse as the geography.

01:01:37.977 --> 01:01:40.713 line:90% position:50% align:center
Guatemala’s official language is Spanish,

01:01:40.713 --> 01:01:45.118 line:90% position:50% align:center
but more than 20 indigenous languages
are also spoken there,

01:01:45.118 --> 01:01:47.120 line:90% position:50% align:center
including Mam.

01:01:47.887 --> 01:01:50.890 line:90% position:50% align:center
More than 500 publishers in 20 congregations

01:01:50.890 --> 01:01:53.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
share the good news in the Mam language.

01:01:54.527 --> 01:01:57.930 line:90% position:50% align:center
These brothers and sisters
are among the 49 publishers

01:01:57.930 --> 01:02:02.435 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the Ostuncalco Mam Congregation
in Quetzaltenango.

01:02:03.369 --> 01:02:07.240 line:90% position:50% align:center
They send you their love and greetings.

01:02:07.240 --> 01:02:10.076 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

01:02:10.076 --> 01:02:12.945 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is JW Broadcasting.

